Now she is the newest board member for Character.org, a national character development nonprofit that provides resources and coaching for schools, organizations, and individuals.
Since 1998, Character.org has certified over 500 National Schools of Character and positively affected over 3 million people.
A Path to ImprovementBecoming a National School of Character is no simple feat, however.
When asked about the end goal for character development, Character.org President and CEO Doug Karr dreams big.
She has served as guest editor for the Journal of Character Education, editor for the Schools of Character Magazine, and manuscript screener in fiction and nonfiction for Autumn House Press.